  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut them into strips</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688466959189-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688466959189-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688466959189-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688466959189-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688466959189-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> pepper strips, red onion wedges </strong>and <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until softened and beginning to colour – these are your <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688466962507-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688466962507-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688466962507-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688466962507-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688466962507-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are in the oven, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688466965248-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688466965248-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688466965248-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688466965248-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688466965248-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>orzo</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688466967909-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688466967909-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688466967909-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688466967909-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688466967909-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat, then once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for an initial 10 min or until the orzo is beginning to soften</p><p>After 10 min, drain, then add your <strong>king prawns </strong>and cook for a remaining 4-5 min or until the orzo is tender and the prawns are cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to prevent it from sticking!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688466970796-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688466970796-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688466970796-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688466970796-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688466970796-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the orzo is cooking, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks (save a few leaves for garnish)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688466973718-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688466973718-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688466973718-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688466973718-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688466973718-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is cooked, add the <strong>roasted vegetables </strong>to the pan with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and stir it all together — this is your <strong>roasted pepper orzo with king prawns</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if your orzo is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted pepper orzo with king prawns</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved basil leaves </strong>and<strong> </strong>a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong>, then season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
